Text.SourceString: Hey {ParentLabel}, look what I found! Old photos of my drawings. I've totally improved since then!
Text.LocalizedString: Hey {ParentLabel}, look what I found! Old photos of my drawings. I've totally improved since then!

Text.SourceString: I whipped up a snack experiment today. It was surprisingly good!
Text.LocalizedString: I whipped up a snack experiment today. It was surprisingly good!

Text.SourceString: Tried baking cookies, but I went overboard with the sugar. They're crazy sweet!
Text.LocalizedString: Tried baking cookies, but I went overboard with the sugar. They're crazy sweet!

Text.SourceString: Made pizza with {SpouseLabel} today. It was awesome, even though the crust got a bit crunchy!
Text.LocalizedString: Made pizza with {SpouseLabel} today. It was awesome, even though the crust got a bit crunchy!

Text.SourceString: Baked some cupcakes and tried a new frosting. Not bad if I say so myself!
Text.LocalizedString: Baked some cupcakes and tried a new frosting. Not bad if I say so myself!

Text.SourceString: Made a smoothie, but I added way too much water. It's basically fruit juice now.
Text.LocalizedString: Made a smoothie, but I added way too much water. It's basically fruit juice now.

Text.SourceString: Hey {ParentLabel}, good morning!
Text.LocalizedString: Hey {ParentLabel}, good morning!

Text.SourceString: Yo {ParentLabel}, what's up? What's for breakfast today?
Text.LocalizedString: Yo {ParentLabel}, what's up? What's for breakfast today?

Text.SourceString: Morning, {ParentLabel}! How about cookies for breakfast?
Text.LocalizedString: Morning, {ParentLabel}! How about cookies for breakfast?

Text.SourceString: I'm exhausted. Can I please crash for a bit longer?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm exhausted. Can I please crash for a bit longer?

Text.SourceString: Hey {ParentLabel}, morning! Did you see the drawing I did last night?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey {ParentLabel}, morning! Did you see the drawing I did last night?

Text.SourceString: Do I have to wake up already?
Text.LocalizedString: Do I have to wake up already?

Text.SourceString: Can I skip school today?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I skip school today?

Text.SourceString: I really don't feel like going to school. Can I just stay home?
Text.LocalizedString: I really don't feel like going to school. Can I just stay home?

Text.SourceString: I'm so tired, I need to crash for a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm so tired, I need to crash for a bit.

Text.SourceString: I'm definitely heading home soon.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm definitely heading home soon.

Text.SourceString: I was practicing guitar in my room. I’m still working on that solo, but I’ll nail it eventually!
Text.LocalizedString: I was practicing guitar in my room. I’m still working on that solo, but I’ll nail it eventually!

Text.SourceString: Hey {ParentLabel}, is it cool if I go hang out at the beach with my friends this weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey {ParentLabel}, is it cool if I go hang out at the beach with my friends this weekend?

Text.SourceString: You won't believe the drama at school right now.//Apparently, there was shouting coming from Emma and Dippa's house last week because a bear—or was it a panda?—broke in and ransacked their kitchen for food!
Text.LocalizedString: You won't believe the drama at school right now.//Apparently, there was shouting coming from Emma and Dippa's house last week because a bear—or was it a panda?—broke in and ransacked their kitchen for food!

Text.SourceString: Have you seen that new challenge on TickTock?//We should do it, {ParentLabel}!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen that new challenge on TickTock?//We should do it, {ParentLabel}!

Text.SourceString: There’s this new game coming out this Summer, Call of Booty: Osmium Ops.//Can we get it? I’m low on funds, and {SpouseLabel} said to ask you.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s this new game coming out this Summer, Call of Booty: Osmium Ops.//Can we get it? I’m low on funds, and {SpouseLabel} said to ask you.

Text.SourceString: I ordered some new green paint. Hope it gets here soon so I can finish up my latest piece.
Text.LocalizedString: I ordered some new green paint. Hope it gets here soon so I can finish up my latest piece.

Text.SourceString: I got some metallic paint on the way. It’s gonna make my art pop once it finally arrives.
Text.LocalizedString: I got some metallic paint on the way. It’s gonna make my art pop once it finally arrives.

Text.SourceString: Can we go to the Shack? I’ve been craving their seafood ramen.//It’s so much better than what we make at home.
Text.LocalizedString: Can we go to the Shack? I’ve been craving their seafood ramen.//It’s so much better than what we make at home.

Text.SourceString: Yesterday, {SpouseLabel} insisted on taking me to school.//I mean, come on, I'm practically an adult now!
Text.LocalizedString: Yesterday, {SpouseLabel} insisted on taking me to school.//I mean, come on, I'm practically an adult now!

Text.SourceString: It feels like everyone else knows what they want to be, and I'm just...lost.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels like everyone else knows what they want to be, and I'm just...lost.

Text.SourceString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.

Special.SourceString: You're not lost, you're exactly where you should be.
Special.LocalizedString: You're not lost, you're exactly where you should be.

Text.SourceString: Really? Thanks, {ParentLabel}. It's good to know I'm not the only one.
Text.LocalizedString: Really? Thanks, {ParentLabel}. It's good to know I'm not the only one.

Special.SourceString: It took a while for me too; you're doing okay.
Special.LocalizedString: It took a while for me too; you're doing okay.

Text.SourceString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.

Text.SourceString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, thanks, {ParentLabel}. That actually makes me feel a little better.

Text.SourceString: Thanks for just listening, {ParentLabel}.
Text.LocalizedString: Thanks for just listening, {ParentLabel}.

Text.SourceString: It's hard to picture what I'll be doing in five years when I can barely decide what to do next week.
Text.LocalizedString: It's hard to picture what I'll be doing in five years when I can barely decide what to do next week.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could change everything about the way I look.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could change everything about the way I look.

Text.SourceString: I know it's silly, but I can't help but think I'm just not cool enough.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it's silly, but I can't help but think I'm just not cool enough.

Text.SourceString: Thanks, {ParentLabel}. I guess it's hard to see it in myself sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Thanks, {ParentLabel}. I guess it's hard to see it in myself sometimes.

Special.SourceString: Oh, darling, you're amazing just the way you are.
Special.LocalizedString: Oh, darling, you're amazing just the way you are.

Text.SourceString: Really? Thanks, {ParentLabel}. I guess it's hard to see it in myself sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Really? Thanks, {ParentLabel}. I guess it's hard to see it in myself sometimes.

Special.SourceString: We all have days when we feel that way, but trust me, you're amazing just as you are.
Special.LocalizedString: We all have days when we feel that way, but trust me, you're amazing just as you are.

Text.SourceString: I guess you're right. Thanks, {ParentLabel}. It's hard to remember that sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess you're right. Thanks, {ParentLabel}. It's hard to remember that sometimes.

Special.SourceString: You're comparing yourself to an unrealistic standard.
Special.LocalizedString: You're comparing yourself to an unrealistic standard.

Text.SourceString: *Say nothing*
Text.LocalizedString: *Say nothing*

Text.SourceString: Ugh, school again...seriously, can we fast-forward to the weekend?
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh, school again...seriously, can we fast-forward to the weekend?

Text.SourceString: Do we have any snacks left? I’m starving!
Text.LocalizedString: Do we have any snacks left? I’m starving!

Text.SourceString: I’ve got practice after school, so don’t wait up for dinner.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve got practice after school, so don’t wait up for dinner.

Text.SourceString: I was going to clean my room, but... I’ll do it later.
Text.LocalizedString: I was going to clean my room, but... I’ll do it later.

Text.SourceString: I feel like the weather can’t make up its mind lately.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like the weather can’t make up its mind lately.

Text.SourceString: Why does time fly when you’re having fun but drag during the boring stuff?
Text.LocalizedString: Why does time fly when you’re having fun but drag during the boring stuff?

Text.SourceString: Does anyone else feel like there’s just not enough hours in the day?
Text.LocalizedString: Does anyone else feel like there’s just not enough hours in the day?

Text.SourceString: I never thought I’d say this, but I miss Summer already.
Text.LocalizedString: I never thought I’d say this, but I miss Summer already.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know about you, {ParentLabel}, but I could live in pajamas and be totally fine with it.//<portrait=annoyed>{SpouseLabel} won't let me though.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know about you, {ParentLabel}, but I could live in pajamas and be totally fine with it.//<portrait=annoyed>{SpouseLabel} won't let me though.

Text.SourceString: What was it like when you were my age, {ParentLabel}?//Did you have TV back in the day?
Text.LocalizedString: What was it like when you were my age, {ParentLabel}?//Did you have TV back in the day?

Text.SourceString: I had a dream that I could fly!
Text.LocalizedString: I had a dream that I could fly!
